10:25.980 --> 10:35.420
In UFOs and the National Security State, you bring up this idea of a breakaway civilization.

10:35.420 --> 10:41.820
And you have Catherine Austin Fitz, this former housing and urban development employee, who

10:41.820 --> 10:46.400
then went on to be a consultant, who's uncovered trillions of dollars worth of fraud.

10:46.800 --> 10:48.080
Discrepancies in accounting, yeah.

10:48.600 --> 10:49.560
Discrepancies in accounting.

10:50.680 --> 10:51.380
Yeah, there you go.

10:51.420 --> 10:52.220
That's a nice euphemism.

10:52.940 --> 10:58.900
So what is a breakaway civilization and what is the nature of the contact that we're seeing?

10:59.060 --> 11:02.780
Yeah, I haven't really thought, I haven't talked a lot about the idea of a breakaway

11:02.780 --> 11:05.720
civilization in a little while, but I still think it's probably true.

11:06.380 --> 11:12.500
And just to give a background, it was a phrase that I coined, I don't know, about almost 20

11:12.500 --> 11:13.100
years ago now.

11:13.760 --> 11:18.640
I do a lot of reading of other types of historians and I was reading a story named Arnold Toynbee.

11:18.800 --> 11:19.560
Some of you know of him.

11:19.620 --> 11:21.560
He writes meta histories of civilizations.

11:21.840 --> 11:25.160
And I was kind of in that headspace and I thought, you know, what is it that actually

11:25.160 --> 11:27.800
makes a civilization distinctive and unique?

11:27.800 --> 11:29.860
And I thought, well, there's a lot of things.

11:29.920 --> 11:34.140
There's like your social structure and your economy and your ideology, your cosmology.

11:34.720 --> 11:38.540
And I thought, you know, if you really think about the classified world, especially like

11:38.540 --> 11:43.540
assuming like the Roswell event or other crash retrievals happened, you have this very, very

11:43.540 --> 11:49.520
deep classified structure that keeps the technology and the science classified away from you and

11:49.520 --> 11:51.760
away from me so that we can't really look at it.

11:52.540 --> 11:55.840
And I thought, well, what do they do with those breakthroughs in their technology?

11:55.840 --> 12:00.940
Well, they're going to learn new things and they're going to privately maybe patent them

12:00.940 --> 12:02.720
and keep them away from the rest of us.

12:02.800 --> 12:05.440
And they're just in danger of running more and more away from this.

12:05.700 --> 12:07.620
Will they have functional flying saucers one day?

12:07.680 --> 12:08.720
Can they go off world?

12:09.020 --> 12:11.740
Can they encounter other beings and all of this?

12:12.060 --> 12:15.780
And I thought, well, they're really actually kind of like a separate civilization when it's

12:15.780 --> 12:17.360
broken away from our own.

12:17.840 --> 12:20.100
And it was a totally theoretical idea.

12:20.220 --> 12:21.080
It still is, I guess.

12:21.180 --> 12:24.980
But I think there's evidence for it in a lot of different ways.

12:24.980 --> 12:26.540
And so that's what I was talking about.

12:26.620 --> 12:33.220
And I think it's a kind of a breakaway group that has its own legal protections and all

12:33.220 --> 12:33.500
of that.

12:34.300 --> 12:36.880
So I've known Catherine Austin Fitz for many years.

12:37.180 --> 12:39.160
I absolutely admire her work.

12:39.260 --> 12:42.620
She's a brilliant financial expert, you could say.

12:42.760 --> 12:43.080
She did.

12:43.800 --> 12:49.460
She served with the first George Bush senior administration back in the late 80s, early 90s

12:49.460 --> 12:52.120
as assistant secretary of housing and urban development.

12:53.280 --> 12:54.720
She told a story.

12:54.840 --> 12:58.100
It should be funny, but it's actually really tragic.

12:58.240 --> 13:02.040
She said, when I went into HUD, I said, I want to look at the accounting.

13:02.140 --> 13:02.900
I want to look at all the books.

13:02.980 --> 13:05.800
And they said, well, no, you're not authorized to see that.

13:06.540 --> 13:08.320
She says, hell, I'm not authorized to see that.

13:08.780 --> 13:09.880
So she finally got her way.

13:09.960 --> 13:13.780
And she said, what happened when they brought in the financial records?

13:13.780 --> 13:17.040
She said, you know, the old library carts with all the books on them, she said, they

13:17.040 --> 13:24.420
wheeled in one after another filled, stacked with papers, like organized, disorganized.

13:24.660 --> 13:28.980
And she's like, God could not pull this apart.

13:29.340 --> 13:34.560
She said, you'd need the greatest accountants in the world to undo this god awful mess.

13:35.200 --> 13:39.980
And she concluded, like, this whole system is designed so that it is impossible to audit.

13:40.560 --> 13:41.940
And that was her start.

13:41.940 --> 13:44.080
And then she goes through four years of that.

13:44.160 --> 13:50.500
And she had her own amazing tumultuous journey dealing with analyzing U.S. government.

13:51.020 --> 13:56.120
And then eventually looking into, she wrote a really great paper called The Myth of the

13:56.120 --> 13:56.720
Rule of Law.

13:56.900 --> 13:57.940
I highly recommend it.

13:58.680 --> 14:03.660
And then she told a really interesting story about, I think, in 1998, she was invited by

14:03.660 --> 14:07.120
a gentleman named John Peterson of the Arlington Institute.

14:07.120 --> 14:12.660
John Peterson was on many, many short lists for DOD Secretary of Defense position for years.

14:13.280 --> 14:14.640
And she wrote about this.

14:14.720 --> 14:21.880
And he said, we're doing a little get-together of a mini-conference to discuss what it would

14:21.880 --> 14:25.500
be like in a world where extraterrestrials are openly acknowledged as living among us.

14:25.500 --> 14:30.960
And she said, the biggest regret in my life was not doing that.

14:31.160 --> 14:31.920
She was afraid.

14:32.220 --> 14:37.640
Because she, at that time, she was looking at connections of the U.S. government and drug

14:37.640 --> 14:40.160
trafficking, intelligence communities, and all of this.

14:40.260 --> 14:42.940
And she knew that they were after her.

14:43.800 --> 14:46.020
And she was afraid that this was like a setup.

14:46.200 --> 14:47.140
And so she didn't do it.

14:47.600 --> 14:49.400
But she, I think she came to regret that.

14:49.600 --> 14:50.500
But anyway, that's Catherine.

14:50.500 --> 14:58.320
And she's come to look at discrepancies in financial doings of the Pentagon and the federal

14:58.320 --> 14:59.100
government in general.

14:59.820 --> 15:07.500
So back in 01, Donald Rumsfeld famously, before the House Armed Services Committee in, I think,

15:07.580 --> 15:09.340
July of 01, just before 9-11.

15:09.340 --> 15:13.260
Now, the Bush administration were brand new at this time.

15:13.380 --> 15:16.980
So in a sense, what he's about to say was no skin off their nose.

15:17.040 --> 15:18.620
This is really indicting Clinton years.

15:18.920 --> 15:21.040
He said, yeah, we've looked at the Pentagon records.

15:21.200 --> 15:24.840
And there's 2 point, I think he said 2.3.

15:25.140 --> 15:26.780
Well, he kept revising it.

15:26.800 --> 15:31.680
But originally, it was $2.3 trillion in unaccounted expenditures.

15:31.680 --> 15:35.540
He said, if you can believe that, chuckle, chuckle, laugh, laugh in the House.

15:35.540 --> 15:39.800
And that became $2.1 trillion on September 10th.

15:39.800 --> 15:40.920
And then came 9-11.

15:42.180 --> 15:44.440
And then you never hear about this again.

15:44.660 --> 15:45.680
That was kind of like gone.

15:46.000 --> 15:52.060
A few months later, there was a guy named Dov Zachheim who took over the accounting of

15:52.060 --> 15:52.500
all of that.

15:52.940 --> 15:54.500
And he, this is like in 2002.

15:54.600 --> 15:55.960
And he's like, yeah, no, we got to figure it out.

15:56.180 --> 15:57.500
It's all done.

15:57.660 --> 16:00.400
We've just, you know, had to look at the books a little more carefully.

16:00.760 --> 16:02.020
And it's down to zero.

16:02.180 --> 16:04.020
We have no more discrepancies.

16:04.920 --> 16:06.420
Literally, that is what he said.

16:06.760 --> 16:09.540
But anyway, so Catherine's been on top of this all these years.

16:09.760 --> 16:13.260
And then the question arises, does this mean the money's missing?

16:13.540 --> 16:17.060
Or is it just you've got accounting discrepancies where you're not getting your books right?

16:17.220 --> 16:18.660
I do think a lot of it is that.

16:18.660 --> 16:21.680
